"01 · THE REAL PROBLEM":"01 · 真正的问题","You are using AI.":"你已经在使用 AI。","But is your work":"但你的工作方式","really changing?":"真的改变了吗？",
"Many people know how to ask AI a question. Fewer know how to help AI understand the real situation.":"很多人会向 AI 提问，却不一定懂得如何让 AI 理解真实情境。",
"You may use ChatGPT, Claude or Gemini to reply to customers, prepare a proposal, plan a project or develop content—yet still receive answers that feel obvious, shallow or difficult to use.":"你可能已经用 ChatGPT、Claude 或 Gemini 回复客户、准备提案、规划项目或制作内容，却仍然得到表面、普通或难以实际采用的答案。",
"Better results begin before the prompt: clarify the problem, organise the context, notice assumptions and decide what a useful answer should help you do.":"更好的结果，始于写提示之前：先厘清问题、整理背景、看见假设，并确定这个答案应该帮助你完成什么。",
"GENERIC OUTPUT":"普通答案","The answer sounds polished but could apply to anyone.":"答案听起来完整，却好像放在任何人身上都适用。",
"MISSING CONTEXT":"缺少背景","AI does not know the people, constraints or priorities behind your task.":"AI 不知道任务背后的人、限制与优先顺序。",
"BLIND ACCEPTANCE":"盲目接受","A confident answer can still be incomplete, unsuitable or wrong.":"语气自信的答案，依然可能不完整、不适合，甚至错误。",
"NO WORKFLOW CHANGE":"工作方式没改变","You generate more content, but your thinking and decisions stay the same.":"你生成了更多内容，但思考与决策方式并没有改变。",
"02 · FOUR COMMON AI MISJUDGEMENTS":"02 · 四个常见 AI 误区","The tool is powerful.":"工具很强大。","How we use it matters.":"关键在于我们如何使用。",
"These habits make AI feel useful at first, but limit the quality of our work over time.":"这些习惯一开始让 AI 看起来很好用，久而久之却会限制工作的质量。",
"Using AI like Google":"把 AI 当成 Google","You keep looking for the “right answer” and miss the chance to explore possibilities, trade-offs and better questions.":"你不断寻找“正确答案”，却错过探索不同可能、取舍与更好问题的机会。","SHIFT → SEARCH TO THINK":"转变 → 从搜索到思考",
"Believing AI is always right":"相信 AI 永远正确","AI gives possibilities, not truth. A confident tone is not evidence that the answer fits your facts or context.":"AI 提供的是可能性，不是真理。语气自信，不代表答案符合事实或你的情境。","SHIFT → VERIFY AND CHALLENGE":"转变 → 验证与挑战",
"Letting AI replace your thinking":"让 AI 取代你的思考","Copying the first answer may save minutes, but it weakens your ability to reason, judge and improve the work.":"复制第一个答案或许省下几分钟，却会削弱推理、判断与改善工作的能力。","SHIFT → THINK FIRST, THEN USE AI":"转变 → 先思考，再用 AI",
"Expecting AI to solve everything":"期待 AI 解决一切","AI handles information well. Trust, leadership, culture, relationships and responsibility still need people.":"AI 擅长处理信息，但信任、领导、文化、关系与责任，仍然需要人。","SHIFT → HUMAN + AI":"转变 → 人类 + AI",
"03 · THE THINKING SHIFT":"03 · 思考方式的转变","A prompt is not a magic sentence.":"提示不是一句魔法咒语。","It is structured thinking.":"它是有结构的思考。",
"AI Prompt Thinking is a simple way to turn an unclear request into a useful thinking conversation.":"AI 思维范式，是把模糊要求转化为有效思考对话的方法。",
"Clarify":"厘清","What are you really trying to solve, decide or create?":"你真正想解决、决定或创造什么？","Context":"背景","What does AI need to know about the people, situation and constraints?":"AI 需要了解哪些人物、情境与限制？","Question":"提问","What should AI analyse, compare, challenge or produce?":"你希望 AI 分析、比较、挑战或产出什么？","What is useful, missing, assumed or potentially wrong?":"哪些内容有用、缺失、未经验证或可能错误？","Improve":"改善","Challenge the answer and refine it step by step.":"挑战答案，并逐步修正。",
"04 · HOW YOUR AI PRACTICE DEVELOPS":"04 · 你的 AI 使用方式如何进阶","Ask and receive.":"提问并接收答案。","Give purpose, context and constraints.":"说明目的、背景与限制。","Review, challenge and improve.":"检视、挑战并改善。","Apply the thinking repeatedly at work.":"把思考方法持续应用在工作中。","The workshop focuses on the practical foundation:":"工作坊聚焦最实用的基础：",
"05 · WHAT YOU WILL PRACTISE":"05 · 你将练习什么","Bring real work.":"带着真实工作情境。","Build useful habits.":"建立真正有用的习惯。","This is not a list of prompt templates to memorise. You will practise a repeatable way to work with AI.":"这不是一堂背诵提示模板的课。你将练习一套可以重复使用的 AI 协作方法。",
"Frame the real problem":"界定真正的问题","Move beyond the first request and identify what actually needs attention.":"不只停留在表面要求，找出真正需要处理的重点。","Give useful context":"提供有用背景","Explain the situation clearly without overwhelming AI with irrelevant details.":"清楚说明情境，同时避免加入无关细节。","Ask from different angles":"从不同角度提问","Explore assumptions, alternatives, risks and blind spots.":"探索假设、替代方案、风险与盲点。","Review AI critically":"批判性检视 AI","Check whether an answer is accurate, useful and appropriate before using it.":"使用前先判断答案是否准确、有用且合适。","Build a thinking loop":"建立思考循环","Improve an answer through feedback instead of accepting the first response.":"透过反馈改善答案，而不是接受第一次回复。","Keep human judgement":"保留人的判断","You remain responsible for what is selected, decided and acted upon.":"最后选择什么、决定什么、采取什么行动，仍由你负责。",
"06 · WHO THIS IS FOR":"06 · 适合谁参加","For people who already use AI—":"适合已经使用 AI，","but want better work.":"但希望把工作做得更好的人。","No technical background is required. This workshop is for people whose work involves thinking, communicating, planning or deciding.":"不需要技术背景。只要你的工作涉及思考、沟通、规划或决策，这个工作坊就适合你。",
